entries.s_12: Neeka! Neeka, right. That's who I am looking for.
entries.s_14: I can't believe you found her. You are always going to be remembered. You have done us a great service.
entries.s_16: Maybe you can help me with the wife now? Eh, nevermind.
entries.s_17: I saw you talking to Kyran. He's a good guy. If he trusts you, then I guess I can too.
entries.s_19: He told me about some slavers near here. I am going to check it out.
entries.s_21: You are? Please could look for my daughter? Her name is Neeka. I am sure she is very scared there all alone.
entries.s_25: I know. I know! I didn't mean to. I thought my wife had her, and she thought I had her. Please you must find her. I don't think I can live knowing what I did. See if you can find Gordo Zek in the slave pens. He always knew what was going on.
entries.s_31: Thank you so much for rescuing Neeka. We'll never forget you.
entries.s_32: I'm sorry friend, but I just don't know you well enough to trust you. Maybe you should talk to Kyran.
